						<summary>

						<p>On the north wall of the central shrine in the Rajatagirīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Rājarāja III. Year 24+1: 1241 A.D.</p>						

						<p>The details of date given <hi rend="italic">viz.</hi>, 24+1st year, Makara ba. 14 Saturday, Uttirāḍam regularly correspond to 1241 A.D., January 12, Saturday.</p>						

						<p>This inscription records the gift of one <hi rend="italic">mā</hi> of land, as <hi rend="italic">araśupēṟu</hi> entrusted to the <hi rend="italic">paḷḷigaḷ</hi> of the land endowed as <hi rend="italic">tirunundāviḷakkuppuṟam</hi>, for supplying oil for a perpetual lamp for god Tiruveḷḷiyaṅguṉṟamuḍaiyār, by the <hi rend="italic">Ūravar</hi> of Tirutteṅgūr Veḷḷiyiḍunagaram in Rājarājaśōḻa-vaḷanāḍu.</p>						

						</summary>
